  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is legally defined as the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or banks. Generally, it involves three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin \n3. Integration - making the funds appear legally obtained\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary somewhat between jurisdictions, but typically involve intentionally disguising the source of criminal proceeds.",
